# Email Conventions

## Sending

- **Single email**: `sendEmail({ to, subject, html })`
- **Bulk (2+)**: Always use `sendEmailBatch(emails[])` — Resend Batch API, max 100 per call
- Never loop `sendEmail()` — Resend rate-limits at 2/sec

## Template

All outbound email must use `emailTemplate(innerHtml, options)`:

```typescript
emailTemplate(
  `<p>Hey ${firstName},</p><p>Your match is tomorrow.</p>`,
  {
    heading: "Senior Framers",           // top banner text
    ctaUrl: "https://framers.app/...",   // big button link
    ctaLabel: "RSVP Now",               // button text
    footerNote: "Optional small print",
  }
)
```

## Sender & BCC

- From: `Greenbrook Framers <captain@framers.app>`
- BCC: `hannes.magnusson@gmail.com` on all emails (automatic in sendEmail/sendEmailBatch)

## Deduplication

For cron-triggered emails, log to `app_events` after sending and check before re-sending:
- `rsvp_reminder` — detail: `{matchId}|{count} recipients` — max once/day per match
- `score_reminder` — detail: `{matchId}|{count} recipients` — max once per 3 days per match

## Webhooks

Resend webhooks hit `/api/webhooks/resend` (signature-verified via `RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET`).
Events logged to `app_events`: `email.delivered`, `email.opened`, `email.clicked`, `email.bounced`, `email.complained`.
